abstract: A respiratory virus that originated in China has infected more than 87,000 people in 60 countries. Almost 3,000 have died.
snippet: A respiratory virus that originated in China has infected more than 87,000 people in 60 countries. Almost 3,000 have died.
lead_paragraph: A novel respiratory virus that originated in Wuhan, China, has spread to more than 60 countries in Asia, Europe and the Middle East, leaving many experts to fear a pandemic may be on the way.

abstract: Many of the elite who gather at the World Economic Forum were horrified by his election. But most seem to have come to accept the U.S. president.

headline_main: Davos Warms to Trump’s Results (if Not Him Personally)

abstract: President Trump made his first appearance on the international stage since the House sent impeachment articles to the Senate, on the day his trial is set to begin in earnest.
snippet: President Trump made his first appearance on the international stage since the House sent impeachment articles to the Senate, on the day his trial is set to begin in earnest.
lead_paragraph: DAVOS, Switzerland — President Trump swept into this moneyed Alpine village on Tuesday, full of brio and flattery, schmoozing with global business leaders as if there were no talk of removing him from office and no impeachment trial unfolding 4,000 miles away in Washington.

abstract: After defending the stop-and-frisk policing tactic, the former mayor  apologized. But black voters in the Democratic presidential race may not forgive him.
snippet: After defending the stop-and-frisk policing tactic, the former mayor  apologized. But black voters in the Democratic presidential race may not forgive him.
lead_paragraph: Two months after jumping into the presidential race, Michael R. Bloomberg has hired staff members in 35 states. He has poured $200 million into advertising. He has crisscrossed the country, visiting dozens of cities far from the standard campaign trail.

abstract: A study that blasted Boeing after a 2009 accident was never made public. Other criticisms were tempered by investigators after the company and U.S. safety officials objected.
snippet: A study that blasted Boeing after a 2009 accident was never made public. Other criticisms were tempered by investigators after the company and U.S. safety officials objected.
lead_paragraph: After a Boeing 737 crashed near Amsterdam more than a decade ago, the Dutch investigators focused blame on the pilots for failing to react properly when an automated system malfunctioned and caused the plane to plummet into a field, killing nine people.

abstract: The decision to endorse two candidates was a significant break with convention. The board said it reflected the Democratic Party’s “radical” and “realist” models.
snippet: The decision to endorse two candidates was a significant break with convention. The board said it reflected the Democratic Party’s “radical” and “realist” models.
lead_paragraph: The New York Times editorial board endorsed the two leading female candidates for the Democratic Party’s presidential nomination on Sunday, throwing its support behind Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota and Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts.

abstract: On his first campaign stop for the Martin Luther King holiday in South Carolina, Joe Biden denounced the president in some of his strongest language yet.
snippet: On his first campaign stop for the Martin Luther King holiday in South Carolina, Joe Biden denounced the president in some of his strongest language yet.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. paid a visit to Sunday services at Bethlehem Baptist Church, a large black congregation here, urging the crowd to fight back against hatred and condemning President Trump in some of his strongest language yet for heightening racial divisions in the country.

abstract: In this week’s Tripped Up column, Sarah Firshein investigates how a family in the Bahamas can recover vacation funds to rebuild their home.
snippet: In this week’s Tripped Up column, Sarah Firshein investigates how a family in the Bahamas can recover vacation funds to rebuild their home.
lead_paragraph: Our family home in the Bahamas was recently destroyed by Hurricane Dorian. Nobody lost their lives, but the physical damage was catastrophic and the emotional trauma is ongoing. I am writing on behalf of my parents, who live there full time.

abstract: Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren argue over what was said at a private 2018 meeting, their dispute takes center stage at the debate and Cory Booker says goodbye.
snippet: Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren argue over what was said at a private 2018 meeting, their dispute takes center stage at the debate and Cory Booker says goodbye.
lead_paragraph: With less than three weeks to go before the Iowa caucuses, tensions escalated between two of the leading Democratic candidates and were on display on national television at a debate in Iowa.
